div.p:
The Hungarian budget shows a revenue of 610 million pre-war pengoes and an
                    expenditure of 710 millions. Expenditure is divided into three categories: 

275 millions for staff salaries and pensions;

125 millions for ordinary maintenance costs;

310 millions for extraordinary maintenance costs,

This being the case, Hungary has a vital interest in obtaining foreign currency;
                    and therefore cannot forego the free disposal of her foreign currency holdings
                    in creditor states.
